<subSubSection id="BCBE9EC6A7FF7CD0A68A393D19D0E5A1" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="63A7A4C700E50174E789481FEC3A8B92" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="CADBF1D59A40730AA688F26E290FB336" authority="Fairmaire, 1887" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pixodarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pixodarus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pixodarus Fairmaire, 1887</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="54E4A4397D9EBE8BD85811E33B03E90A" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" type="type species">
<paragraph id="E012808632BFA54977CCE4EC7818F913" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8D5B12B530A5118FB8C3661361438C5" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="63EE1C8778A314EF282BA24E99B3790B" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hoplideres" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hoplideres nyassae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nyassae">Hoplideres nyassae</taxonomicName>
Bates, 1878
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="419F5D93472F1ADE3C2B9FA0AE3F4F72" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
In their revision of the African and Madagascan 
<taxonomicName id="AB6AA6E69DDC5BFCDAD332E8E2279B7E" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" rank="tribe" tribe="Hopliderini">Hopliderini</taxonomicName>
(then referred to as subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="73E4B2FBABEF52E272DD53235652713A" genus="Hopliderina" lsidName="Hopliderina" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" rank="subtribe" subtribe="Hopliderina">Hopliderina</taxonomicName>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="9B2F9590A9A8499FC9D1A4F7E3CA02C8" author="Quentin, RM" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (NS)" pageId="13" pageNumber="90" pagination="257 - 289" title="Revision des Hoploderina africains et malgaches (Col. CerambycidaePrioninae)." volume="8" year="1972">Quentin and Villiers (1972)</bibRefCitation>
cautioned strongly in their preamble about treating this group carefully: &quot;due to the extreme variability of a number of characters&quot; (l.c. p. 258). As examples of this extreme variability, they listed characters like the longitudinal furrow of the head, the length and number of spines on the antennae and 
<pageBreakToken id="0B859099A56868DA3D442AA4E997FD7E" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" start="start">antennomeres</pageBreakToken>
, the shape, sculpture and number of lateral spines on the pronotum, the spines and denticulation of the humeral and posthumeral margins of the elytra, and the pubescence on the ventral surface and tibiae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D0386B17F27B3DB7B9379CAC2B958283" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
In spite of these cautionary remarks, 
<bibRefCitation id="6238C80DA952D4621C1F5AD300E4CCD8" author="Quentin, RM" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (NS)" pageId="13" pageNumber="90" pagination="257 - 289" title="Revision des Hoploderina africains et malgaches (Col. CerambycidaePrioninae)." volume="8" year="1972">Quentin and Villiers (1972)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="32937D05CAA82A4C8EBE651360B32BD0" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pixodarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pixodarus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pixodarus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3B64EDC5ACC439AD686850BBFCE34DF1" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pixodarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pixodarus exasperatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exasperatus">Pixodarus exasperatus</taxonomicName>
, based on very subtle characters. These included the raised parts of the pronotal vermiculations being glossy or not, variations in shades of reddish-brown to black in the colour of the elytra, as well as small differences in elytral length/width ratios.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A6750AD3C5ABD731A003240FB7D1838F" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
<taxonomicName id="0540DD21B517D2B0E5C7CD23AAFE9141" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pixodarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pixodarus nyassae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nyassae">Pixodarus nyassae</taxonomicName>
is known from RSA and Mozambique northwards to Zimbabwe and Malawi, while 
<taxonomicName id="D325BDB874685920B56576624D7C86D7" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pixodarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pixodarus exasperatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exasperatus">Pixodarus exasperatus</taxonomicName>
occurs in Tanzania, southern Kenya and the eastern part of the Democratic Republic of Congo (
<bibRefCitation id="E2B577A11EB365289E40383CF77BA408" author="Quentin, RM" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (NS)" pageId="13" pageNumber="90" pagination="257 - 289" title="Revision des Hoploderina africains et malgaches (Col. CerambycidaePrioninae)." volume="8" year="1972">Quentin and Villiers 1972</bibRefCitation>
). During the course of this study, the authors have examined a number of specimens from RSA and Mozambique, as well as from Tanzania. We find great variation in all diagnostic characters mentioned both in the southern and the northern populations, and these variations strongly overlap. We therefore endorse the earlier proposal of 
<bibRefCitation id="792E6FC27CC54A44CD49A92953AB28DE" author="Santos Ferreira, GW" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs van die Nasionale Museum, Bloemfontein" pageId="13" pageNumber="90" pagination="1 - 335" title="The Parandrinae and the Prioninae of Southern Africa (Cerambycidae, Coleoptera)." volume="13" year="1980">Santos Ferreira (1980)</bibRefCitation>
to synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="08D0FB9D23BF26BF8192958BBC98F822" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pixodarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pixodarus exasperatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exasperatus">Pixodarus exasperatus</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="F9EB23F377F56968D037E77988916E7C" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pixodarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pixodarus nyassae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nyassae">Pixodarus nyassae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0DA704D144095E7136131EC3A42D4966" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
On the other hand, the female erroneously included in the description of 
<taxonomicName id="6B65A80E8B4726A78D8C498E632AEEC2" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Afraustraloderes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afraustraloderes rassei" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rassei">Afraustraloderes rassei</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="6857D7109C1A6EA0344FC9F35A3C6651" author="Bouyer, T" journalOrPublisher="Lambillionea" pageId="12" pageNumber="89" pagination="213 - 217" title="Description d'un nouveau genre et d'une nouvelle espece d'Hopliderini d'Afrique du Sud (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Prioninae)." volume="112" year="2012">Bouyer (2012)</bibRefCitation>
represents a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="558FB3CFB96C76B1E0B59C074C78CE3B" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pixodarus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pixodarus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pixodarus</taxonomicName>
and, together with the recently obtained male, is described as a new species below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
